.
This doesn&#39;t belong in an OSG VO GOC ticket, but I don&#39;t see any way to report software bugs, so I&#39;m putting it here.

I am having an issue with lcg-cp, in that I can&#39;t find any documentation on the timeout options or what they mean and what the defaults are.  The error message I get from using the &#34;-t&#34; option tells me to use the --timeout-* options, but those actually appear to be called --*-timeout, and in any case I can&#39;t make sense of how to set them.

The latest gLite manual (EDMS 722398 v1.4.1 from Aug 3 2011) still shows the -t option for lcg-cp.  I&#39;d report the problem in CERN Savannah, but I can&#39;t post bugs there!

So, five things (in order of importance)&#58;

1. Please advise on timeouts for lcg-cp command and how to set these &#34;sensibly&#34; for a 5-15 MB transfer from UCSD to some OSG WN.

2. Please advise on where I can get up to date documentation on lcg-cp.

3. Please put man pages in place for key OSG tools like lcg-cp.

4. Please correct error/warning messages in lcg-cp (and ideally include more verbose in-binary documentation if no man pages are available).

5. Please provide a pointer on how software bugs are meant to be reported.

Thanks!

Ian

PS - a bonus request would be to include a -q/--quiet option that would reduce the verbosity of lcg-cp output.</pre></div><legend>Similar Recent Tickets <small>modified within the last 30 days</small></legend><div id="similar_tickets"><p class="muted">No similar tickets found.</p></div>
